    "vorm": "<b>ἄγω</b>,",
    "definitie": "<br/>1. <em>to lead, bring, carry</em>: c. acc., seq. <span class=\"greek\">ἐπί</span>, <span class=\"greek\">εἰς</span>, <span class=\"greek\">ἕως</span>, <span class=\"greek\">πρός</span> and simple dat.; metaph., <em>to lead, guide, impel</em>: Jo 10:16 Ro 2:4, He 2:10, II Ti 3:6, al. <br/>2. <em>to spend</em> or <em>keep</em> a day: Lk 24:21, Ac 19:38 <br/>3. Intrans., <em>to go</em>: subjunc., <span class=\"greek\">ἄγωμεν</span>, Mt 2:46, al. (Cramer, 61; MM, <i>VGT</i>, s.v.).",
