  "G114": {
    "woord": "ἀθετέω",
    "gloss": "to set aside, disregard",
    "vorm": "† <b>ἀθετέω</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ῶ</span>",
    "definitie": "<br/>1. <em>to set aside, disregard</em> (in Gramm., <em>to reject as spurious</em>): <span class=\"greek\">διαθήκην</span>, Ga 3:16; <span class=\"greek\">ἐντολήν</span>, Mk 7:9; <span class=\"greek\">νόμον</span>, He 10:28; <span class=\"greek\">πίστιν</span>, I Ti 5:12. <br/>2. <em>to nullify, make void</em>: Lk 7:30 (v. Field, <i>Notes</i>, 59), I Co 1:19, Ga 2:21. <br/>3. <em>to reject</em>: Mk 6:26 (Field, op. cit., 30), Lk 10:16, Jo 12:48, I Th 4:8, Ju 8 (for exx. in <span class=\"greek\">π.</span>, v. MM, <i>VGT</i>, s.v.).†",
    "nt": "16",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">τίθημι</span>), [in LXX for seventeen different words, <span class=\"hebrew\">פּשׁע</span>, <span class=\"hebrew\">מרד</span>, <span class=\"hebrew\">בּגד</span>, <span class=\"hebrew\">מעל</span>, etc., often meaning, as I Ki 13:3 (Heb., al.), <i>to revolt</i>; properly, <i>to make</i> <span class=\"greek\">ἄθετον</span>, or <i>do away with what has been laid down</i> (v. <i>DCG</i>, i, 453 f.)]."
  },
