  "G225": {
    "woord": "ἀλήθεια",
    "gloss": "truth",
    "vorm": "<b>ἀλήθεια</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ας, ἡ</span>",
    "definitie": "<em>truth</em> (v. <i>DB</i>, iv, 818f.). <br/>1. Objectively, \"the reality lying at the basis of an appearance; the manifested, veritable essence of a matter\" (Cremer, 86): Ro 9:1, al.; of religious truth, Ro 1:25, al.; esp. of Christian doctrine, Ga 2:5, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἀ. θεοῦ</span>, Ro 15:8. <br/>2. Subjectively, <em>truthfulness, truth</em>, not merely verbal (cl.), but sincerity and integrity of character: Jo 8:44, III Jo 3. <br/>3. In phrases (MM, <i>VGT</i>, s.v.): <span class=\"greek\">ἐπ’ ἀληθείας</span>, Mk 12:14, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἀ. λέγειν</span> (<span class=\"greek\">εἰπεῖν</span>, <span class=\"greek\">λαλεῖν</span>), Ro 9:1, II Co 12:6, Eph 4:25, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἀ. ποιεῖν</span>, Jo 3:21, I Jo 1:6 (cf. <i>DB</i>, iv, 818b, ff.).",
    "nt": "109",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">ἀληθής</span>), [in LXX chiefly for <span class=\"hebrew\">אֱמֶת</span> (on which, v. Cremer, 627f.), <span class=\"hebrew\">אֱמוּנָה</span>;]"
  },
  "G226": {
    "woord": "ἀληθεύω",
    "gloss": "to speak the truth",
    "vorm": "<b>ἀληθεύω</b>",
    "definitie": "<em>to speak the truth</em> (R, mg., <i>deal truly</i>; Field, <i>Notes</i>, 192): Ga 4:16, Eph 4:15.†",
    "nt": "2",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">ἀληθής</span>), [in LXX: Ge 20:16 (<span class=\"hebrew\">יָכַח</span>) Ge 42:16 (<span class=\"hebrew\">אֶמֶת</span>), Pr 21:3 (<span class=\"hebrew\">מִשְׁפָּט</span>), Is 44:26 (<span class=\"hebrew\">שָׁלַם</span>), Si 34:4*;]"
  },
  "G227": {
    "woord": "ἀληθής",
    "gloss": "true",
    "vorm": "<b>ἀληθής</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ές</span>",
    "definitie": "of things, <em>true</em>, conforming to reality: Jo 4:18 5:31,32 6:55 (= <span class=\"greek\">ἀληθινός</span>, q.v.) Jo 8:13,14, 17 10:41 19:35 21:24, Ac 12:9, Phl 4:8, Tit 1:13, I Pe 5:12, II Pe 2:22, I Jo 2:8, III Jo 12;",
    "nt": "25",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">λήθω</span> = <span class=\"greek\">λανθάνω</span>, hence primarily, <i>unconcealed, manifest</i>; hence, <i>actual, real</i>), [in LXX for <span class=\"hebrew\">אֶמֶת</span>, etc.;]"
  },
  "G228": {
    "woord": "ἀληθινός",
    "gloss": "true",
    "vorm": "<b>ἀληθινός</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ή, -όν</span>",
    "definitie": "<em>true</em>, in the sense of real, ideal, genuine: Lk 16:11 Jo 1:9 4:23, 37 6:32 7:28 8:16 15:1 17:3 19:35, I Th 1:9, He 8:2 9:24 10:22, I Jo 2:8 5:20, Re 3:7, 14 6:10 15:3 16:7 19:2; = <span class=\"greek\">ἀληθής</span>, Re 19:9 21:5 22:6 (MM, <i>VGT</i>, s.v.).†",
    "nt": "28",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">ἀληθής</span>), [in LXX for <span class=\"hebrew\">אֶמֶת</span>;]"
  },
