    "gloss": "uncircumcised",
    "vorm": "† <b>ἀ-περί-τμητος</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ον</span>",
    "definitie": "<em>uncircumcised</em>; metaph. (<span class=\"greek\">τ.</span>) <span class=\"greek\">καρδίαις</span> (cf. Je 9:26, al.): Ac 7:51. (<span class=\"greek\">ἄσημος</span>, found in <span class=\"greek\">π.</span>, appears to have been the word used by Greek-speaking Egyptians: v. Deiss., <i>BS</i>, 153; cf. also Cremer, 885; MM, s.v.)†",
