    "definitie": "<em>the right</em>: Mt 5:29, Jo 18:10, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ὅπλα δ.</span>, weapons carried in the right hand, i.e. for offence, II Co 6:7 ; <span class=\"greek\">ἡ δ. χείρ</span>, Mt 5:30, Lk 6:6, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἡ δ.</span> (sc. <span class=\"greek\">χείρ</span>), Mt 6:3, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἐπὶ τὴν δ.</span>, <em>in the right hand</em> (R, txt., <i>on</i> R, mg.), Re 5:1; <span class=\"greek\">διδόναι τὴν δ.</span>, in friend­ship (Deiss., <i>BS</i>, 251), Ga 2:9; metaph. of power, <span class=\"greek\">τῇ δ. αὐτοῦ</span>, Ac 2:33 5:31; <span class=\"greek\">τὰ δ.</span>, <em>the right side</em>, Mk 16:5; <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ δεξιῶν</span>, <em>on the right hand</em>, c. gen., Mt 25:33, 34, Mk 15:27, Lk 1:11, al.; of a place of honour in the Messianic Kingdom (cf. III Ki 2:19, Ps 44(45):10), <span class=\"greek\">καθίσαι ἐκ δεξιῶν</span>, Mt 20:21, Mk 10:37; of the heavenly session of Christ, Mt 26:64, Mk 14:62, He 1:13 (Cremer, 172)",
