    "gloss": "because",
    "vorm": "<b>δι-ότι </b>, conjunct., for <span class=\"greek\">διὰ τοῦτο, ὅτι</span> (Lat. propterea quod),",
    "definitie": "<em>because</em>: Lk 1:13 2:7 21:28, Ac 13:35 18:10 20:26 22:18, Ro 1:19, 21 3:20 8:7, 21, I Co 15:9, Phl 2:26, I Th 2:8, 18 (Lft., <i>Notes</i>, 37) 4:6, He 11:5, 23, Ja 4:3, I Pe 1:16, 24 2:6. It is usually stronger than <span class=\"greek\">ὅτι</span>, but sometimes, as in Lk 1:13, Ro 1:19, I Th 2:18, approximates to MGr. sense, <em>for</em>; cf. Milligan, <i>Th.</i>, l.c.†",
