    "woord": "ἐσθίω",
    "gloss": "to eat",
    "vorm": "<b>ἐσθίω</b>, and (poet, and late prose) <span class=\"greek\">ἔσθω</span>,",
    "definitie": "<em>to eat</em>; <br/>(a) absol.: Mt 14:20, 21 Mk 6:31, Jo 4:31, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἐν τ. φαγεῖν</span> (on this aor. form, v. M, <i>Pr.</i>, 111), I Co 11:21; <span class=\"greek\">διδόναι φαγεῖν</span>, c. dat. pers., Mk 5:43, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἐ. καὶ πίνειν</span>, Mt 6:25, 31 Lk 10:7, al.; of ordinary use of food and drink, I Co 9:4 11:22; of partaking of food at table, Mk 2:16, Lk 5:30, al.; opp. to fasting, Mt 11:18, Lk 5:33, al.; of revelling, Mt 24:49, Lk 12:45 . <br/>(b) c. acc. rei: Mt 6:25, Mk 1:6, Jo 6:31, Ro 14:2, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἄρτον</span> (Heb. <span class=\"hebrew\">אָכַל לֶחֶם</span>), Mt 15:2, Mk 3:20, al.; <span class=\"greek\">τὸν ἑαυτοῦ ἄ.</span>, II Th 3:12; <span class=\"greek\">ἄ.</span> seq. <span class=\"greek\">παρά</span>, gen. pers., II Th 3:8; <span class=\"greek\">τά</span> seq. id., Lk 10:7; <span class=\"greek\">τ. πάσχα</span>, Mt 26:17, Mk 14:12 al; <span class=\"greek\">τ. κυριακὸν δεῖπνον</span>, I Co 11:20; <span class=\"greek\">τ. θυσίας</span>, I Co 10:18; seq. <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ</span> (= cl. part. gen.), Jo 6:26, 50, 51, I Co 11:28; <span class=\"greek\">ἀπό</span> (cf. Heb. <span class=\"hebrew\">אָכַל מִן</span>), Mt 15:27, Mk 7:28; metaph., <em>to devour, consume</em>: He 10:27, Ja 5:3, Re 17:16 (cf. <span class=\"greek\">κατ-, συν-εσθίω</span>) .",
