  "G2087": {
    "woord": "ἕτερος",
    "gloss": "other",
    "vorm": "<b>ἕτερος</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-α, -ον</span>,",
    "definitie": "distributive pron., prop. dual (Bl., §13, 5; 51, 6), denoting the second of a pair, but in late Gk. encroaching on <span class=\"greek\">ἄλλος</span> (M, <i>Pr.</i>, 79 f.); <br/>1. of number, <em>other</em>; c. art., <em>the other</em>; <br/>(a) of two, Lk 5:7 9:56, al.; opp. to <span class=\"greek\">ὁ πρῶτος</span>, Mt 21:30; <span class=\"greek\">ὁ εἷς</span>, Mt 6:24, Lk 7:41, Ac 23:6, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἕ. μὲν . . . ἕ. δέ</span>, <em>the one . . . the other</em>: I Co 15:40; <em>the next</em>: Lk 6:6 9:56 (sc. <span class=\"greek\">ἡμέρα</span>, Xen.), Ac 20:15 27:3; = <span class=\"greek\">ὁ πλησίον</span>, <em>one's neighbour</em>: Ro 2:1 13:8, I Co 6:1, al.; <br/>(b) of more than two, <em>another</em>: Mt 8:21 11:3, Lk 6:6 22:65, Jo 19:37, Ro 8:39, al.; pl., Ac 2:13; <span class=\"greek\">οἱ μὲν . . . ἄλλοι δὲ . . . ἕ. δέ</span>, Mt 16:14; <span class=\"greek\">τινὲς . . . ἕ. δέ</span>, Lk 11:16. <br/>2. Of kind or quality, <em>other, another, different</em> (Plat., Dem., al.): Mk 16:[12], Lk 9:29, Ac 2:4, I Co 14:21, II Co 11:4, Ga 1:6, al. (cf. <span class=\"greek\">ἑτερό-γλωσσος, -διδασκαλέω, -ζυγέω</span>).",
    "nt": "98",
    "etymologie": "[in LXX chiefly for <span class=\"hebrew\">אַחֵר</span> ;]"
  },
