  "G2228": {
    "woord": "ἤ",
    "gloss": "or",
    "vorm": "<b>ἤ</b>,",
    "definitie": "<br/>1. disjunctive, <em>or</em>; <br/>(a) between single words: Mt 5:17, Mk 6:56, Lk 2:24, Jo 6:19, Ro 1:21, al.; <br/>(b) before a sentence expressing a variation, denial or refutation of a previous statement, freq. in interrog. form: Mt 7:4, 9, Mk 12:14, Lk 13:4, Ro 3:29 6:3 9:21, I Co 6:9, 16 9:6, II Co 11:7; <span class=\"greek\">ἢ . . . ἤ</span>, <em>either . . . or</em>, Mt 6:24, Lk 16:13, I Co 14:6; <br/>(c) in a disjunctive question (as Lat. an after utrum): Mt 9:5, Mk 2:9, Lk 7:19, al.; after <span class=\"greek\">πότερον</span>, Jo 7:17; <span class=\"greek\">μή</span>, I Co 9:8; <span class=\"greek\">μήτι</span>, II Co 1:17; <span class=\"greek\">ἢ . . . ἢ . . . ἤ</span>, Mk 13:35. <br/>2. Comparative, <em>than</em>: after comparatives, Mt 10:15, Lk 9:13, Jo 3:19, Ro 13:11, al.; after <span class=\"greek\">ἕτερον</span>, Ac 17:21; <span class=\"greek\">θέλω</span> (Khüner<sup>3</sup>, ɪᴠ, 303), I Co 14:19; <span class=\"greek\">πρὶν ἤ</span>, <em>before</em>, seq. acc. et inf., Mt 1:18, Mk 14:30; after a positive adj. (Ge 49:12; cf. Robertson, <i>Gr.</i>, 661), Mt 18:8, 9, Mk 9:43, 45, 47. <br/>3. With other particles: <span class=\"greek\">ἀλλ’ ἤ</span>, v.s. <span class=\"greek\">ἀλλά</span>; <span class=\"greek\">ἢ γάρ</span>, v.s. <span class=\"greek\">γάρ</span>; <span class=\"greek\">ἢ καί</span>, <em>or even</em>, <em>or also</em>, Mt 7:10, Lk 11:11, 12, Ro 2:15 4:9, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ἤτοι . . . ἤ</span>, Ro 6:16 (cf. Wi 11:19).",
    "nt": "332"
  },
