  "G2316": {
    "woord": "θεός",
    "gloss": "a god or deity",
    "vorm": "<b>θεός</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-οῦ, ὁ, ἡ</span> (Ac 19:37 only; v. M, <i>Pr.</i>, 60, 244), late voc., <span class=\"greek\">θεέ</span> (Mt 27:46; cf. De 3:24, al.),",
    "definitie": "<em>a god or deity</em>, <em>God</em>. <br/>1. In polytheistic sense, <em>a god</em> or <em>deity</em>: Ac 28:6, I Co 8:4, II Th 2:4, al.; pl., Ac. 14:11 19:26, Ga 4:8, al. <br/>2. Of the one true <em>God</em>; <br/>(a) anarthrous: Mt 6:24, Lk 20:38, al.; esp. c. prep. (Kühner<sup>3</sup>, iii, 605), <span class=\"greek\">ἀπὸ θ.</span>, Jo 3:2; <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ</span>, Ac 5:39, II Co 5:1, Phl 3:9; <span class=\"greek\">ὑπό</span>, Ro 13:1; <span class=\"greek\">παρὰ θεοῦ</span>, Jo 1:6; <span class=\"greek\">παρὰ θεῷ</span>, II Th 1:6, I Pe 2:4; <span class=\"greek\">κατὰ θεόν</span>, Ro 8:27, II Co 7:9, 10; also when in gen. dependent on an anarth. noun (Bl., §46, 6), Mt 27:43, Lk 3:2, Ro 1:17, I Th 2:13; as pred., Lk 20:38, Jo 1:1, and when the nature and character rather than the person of God is meant, Ac 5:29, Ga 2:6, al. (M, <i>Th.</i>, 14); <br/>(b) more freq., c. art.: Mt 1:23, Mk 2:7, al. mult.; c. prep., <span class=\"greek\">ἀπὸ τ. θ.</span>, Lk 1:26; <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ</span>, Jo 8:42, al.; <span class=\"greek\">παρὰ τοῦ θ.</span>, Jo 8:40; <span class=\"greek\">π. τῷ θ.</span>, Ro 9:14; <span class=\"greek\">ἐν</span>, Col 3:3; <span class=\"greek\">ἐπὶ τῷ θ.</span>, Lk 1:47; <span class=\"greek\">ἐπὶ τὸν θ.</span>, Ac 15:19; <span class=\"greek\">εἰς τ. θ.</span>, Ac 24:15; <span class=\"greek\">πρὸς τ. θ.</span>, Jo 1:2; c. gen. pers., Mt 22:32, Mk 12:26, 27, Lk 20:37, Jo 20:17, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ὁ θ. μου</span>, Ro 1:8, Phl 1:3, al.; <span class=\"greek\">ὁ θ. καὶ πατήρ κ. τ. λ.</span>, Ro 15:6, Eph 1:3, Phl 4:20, al.; c. gen. rei, Ro 15:5, 13, 33, II Co 1:3, I Th 5:23; <span class=\"greek\">τὰ τ. θεοῦ</span>, Mt 16:23, Mk 12:17, I Co 2:11; <span class=\"greek\">τὰ πρὸς τὸν θ.</span>, Ro 15:17, He 2:17 5:1; <span class=\"greek\">τ. θεῷ</span>, as a superl. (LXX, Jos 3:3), Ac 7:20, II Co 10:4; Hebraistically, of judges (Ps 81(82):6), Jo 10:34<sup>(LXX)</sup>, 35.",
    "nt": "1307",
    "etymologie": "[in LXX chiefly for <span class=\"hebrew\">אֱלֹהִים</span>, also for <span class=\"hebrew\">אֵל</span> and other cognate forms, <span class=\"hebrew\">יהוה</span>, etc.;]"
  },
  "G2317": {
    "woord": "θεοσέβεια",
    "gloss": "fear of God",
    "vorm": "<b>θεοσέβεια</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-ας, ἡ</span>",
    "definitie": "<em>fear of God</em>, <em>godliness</em>: I Ti 2:10.†",
    "nt": "1",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">θεοσεβής</span>), [in LXX: Ge 20:11 (<span class=\"hebrew\">אֱלֹהִים</span> <span class=\"hebrew\">יִרְאַה</span>), Jb 28:28 (<span class=\"hebrew\">אֲדֹנָי</span> id.), Si 1:24, Ba 5:4, IV Mac 7:6, 22, <span class=\"hebrew\">א</span> IV Mac 15:28 <span class=\"hebrew\">א</span> IV Mac 17:15*;]"
  },
