  "G3319": {
    "woord": "μέσος",
    "gloss": "middle",
    "vorm": "<b>μέσος</b>, <span class=\"greek\">-η, -ον</span>,",
    "definitie": "<em>middle</em>, <em>in the middle</em> or <em>midst</em>; <br/>1. prop., as an adj.: Lk 23:45, Jo 19:18, Ac 1:18; c. gen. pl., Lk 22:55, Jo 1:26; gen. temp. (Bl., § 36, 13), <span class=\"greek\">μέσης νυκτός</span>, Mt 25:6; <span class=\"greek\">μ. ἡμέρας</span>, Ac 26:13. <br/>2. In adverbial phrases, neut., <span class=\"greek\">μέσον, τὸ μ.</span>, as subst.: <span class=\"greek\">ἀνὰ μέσον</span>, c. gen., <em>between</em> (cl.; in LXX: Ge 1:4, al.), elliptically (but v. M, <i>Pr.</i>, 99), I Co 6:5; = <span class=\"greek\">ἐν μ.</span>, <em>among</em>, <em>in the midst of</em> (Bl., § 39, 2; 40, 8; cf. in LXX: Jos 19:1, Si 27:2), Mt 13:25, Mk 7:31, Re 7:17; <span class=\"greek\">διὰ μέσου</span>, c. gen., Lk 4:30; <span class=\"greek\">διὰ μέσον</span> (Rec. <span class=\"greek\">-ου</span>, v. Bl., § 42, 1), <em>between</em>, Lk 17:11 (<i>ICC</i>, in l.); <span class=\"greek\">εἰς τὸ μ.</span> (v.s. <span class=\"greek\">εἰς</span>), Mk 3:3, Lk 4:35 5:19 6:8, Jo 20:19, 26; <span class=\"greek\">εἰς μ.</span>, Mk 14:60; <span class=\"greek\">ἐν τῷ μ.</span>, Mt 14:6; <span class=\"greek\">ἐν μ.</span>, Jos 8:[3, 9], Ac 4:7; c, gen. loc., Mk 6:47, Lk 21:21 22:55, Ac 17:22, He 2:12<sup>(LXX)</sup>, Re 4:6 5:6 22:2. c. gen. pl., Mt 10:16 18:2, 20, Mk 9:36, Lk 2:46 8:7 10:3 22:27 24:36, Ac 1:15 2:22 27:21, I Th 2:7, Re 1:13 2:1 5:6 6:6; <span class=\"greek\">κατὰ μέσον τ. νυκτός</span>, Ac 27:27 (Bl., § 47, 6); <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ τοῦ μ.</span> (Lft., in l.; Deiss., <i>BS</i>, 252 f.), Col 2:14; <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ μ.</span>, II Th 2:7; <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ τοῦ μ.</span>, c. gen., Mt 13:49, Ac 17:33 23:10, I Co 5:2, II Co 6:17. <br/>3. Neut., <span class=\"greek\">μέσον</span>, adverbially, c. gen., <em>in the midst of</em>, Mt 14:24 (WH, txt., R, mg., aliter), Phl 2:15 (<span class=\"greek\">διὰ μέσου</span>—v. supr.—also Jo 8:50, R, mg.).†",
    "nt": "58",
    "etymologie": "[in LXX chiefly for <span class=\"hebrew\">תָּוֶךְ</span>;]"
  },
