    "gloss": "to commit adultery",
    "vorm": "<b>μοιχεύω</b>",
    "definitie": "<em>to commit adultery</em>: absol., Mt 5:27 19:18, Mk 10:19, Lk 16:18 18:20, Ro 2:22 13:9, Ja 2:11; c. acc. fem., Mt 5:28. Pass., of the woman, Mt 5:32 19:9 WH, mg.), Jo 8:[4]. Metaph., of idolatry (v.s. <span class=\"greek\">μιοιχαλίς</span>, and cf. Je 3:9, al.), seq. <span class=\"greek\">μετ’ αὐτῆς</span>, Re 2:22.†",
    "nt": "15",
    "etymologie": "(< <span class=\"greek\">μοιχός</span>), [in LXX: Ex 20:13, Le 20:10, al. (<span class=\"hebrew\">נאף</span>);]"
