    "definitie": "<em>to disturb, trouble, stir up</em>: primarily in physical sense (Hom., Eur.): <span class=\"greek\">τ. ὕδωρ</span>, Jo 1:5 [4], 7. Metaph., of the mind (Æsch., Plat., al.), <em>to trouble, disquiet, perplex</em>: Ac 15:24, Ga 1:7 5:10; <span class=\"greek\">ἑαυτόν</span> (<em>troubled himself</em>; Westc., in l.), Jo 11:33; of a crowd, <em>to stir up</em>, Ac 17:8, 13; pass., Mt 2:3 14:26, Mk 6:50, Lk 1:12 24:38, Jo 12:27 (Ps 5 (6):4) Ps 14:1, 27, I Pe 3:14 <sup>(LXX)</sup>; <span class=\"greek\">τ. πνεύματι</span>, Jo 13:21 (cf. <span class=\"greek\">δια-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">ἐκ-ταράσσω</span>)",
