  "G5143": {
    "woord": "τρέχω",
    "gloss": "to run",
    "vorm": "<b>τρέχω </b>",
    "definitie": "<em>to run</em>: Mk 5:6, Jo 20:2, 4, I Co 9:24, 26; c. inf., Mt 28:8; seq. <span class=\"greek\">ἐπί</span>, Lk 24:12 [T |[WH]| R, mg., om.]; <span class=\"greek\">εἰς</span>, Re 9:9; ptcp., <span class=\"greek\">δραμών</span>, c. indic., Mt 27:48, Mk 15:36, Lk 15:20. Metaph., from runners in a race, of swiftness or of effort to attain an end: Ro 9:16, Ga 2:2 5:7, Phl 2:16; <span class=\"greek\">τ. ἀγῶνα</span> (Hdt., Eur., al.), He 12:1; <span class=\"greek\">ὁ λόγος τ. κυρίου</span> (cf. Ps 147:4 (146<sup>15</sup>), <span class=\"greek\">ἕως τάχους δραμεῖται ὁ λ. αὐτοῦ</span>), II Th 3:1 (cf. <span class=\"greek\">εἰς-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">κατα-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">περι-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">προ-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">προσ-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">συν-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">ἐπι-συν-</span>, <span class=\"greek\">ὑπο-τρέχω</span>).†",
    "nt": "20",
    "etymologie": "[in LXX chiefly for <span class=\"hebrew\">רוּץ</span> ;]"
  },
